990
01:18:28,788 --> 01:18:30,498
What the hell can I say to you
to stop you?

991
01:18:30,582 --> 01:18:32,876
Why would you want to, Chuck? Why?

992
01:18:32,959 --> 01:18:34,794
Because climbing down there
when it's dark

993
01:18:34,878 --> 01:18:38,047
is a thin step short of suicide,
that's why.

994
01:18:38,131 --> 01:18:41,551
Okay, maybe you better sit
this one out then.

995
01:18:43,136 --> 01:18:46,431
You brought me into this, boss,
and now we're trapped here

996
01:18:46,514 --> 01:18:50,184
on this rock, on this island,
with no one to rely on but each other,

997
01:18:50,268 --> 01:18:52,228
and now you're acting like...

998
01:18:52,312 --> 01:18:55,315
Like what? Like what? How am I acting?

999
01:19:00,153 --> 01:19:03,615
What the hell happened back there
in those cells, Ted?

1000
01:19:08,328 --> 01:19:11,581
What do you think the weather's like
in Portland, Chuck?

1001
01:19:11,664 --> 01:19:13,333
I'm from Seattle.

1002
01:19:15,960 --> 01:19:17,211
Seattle.

1003
01:19:20,423 --> 01:19:23,176
I'm going on alone.

1004
01:19:26,095 --> 01:19:28,973
- I'm going with you, boss.
- I said alone.

1005
01:19:30,683 --> 01:19:31,809
Fine.

1006
01:19:58,461 --> 01:19:59,712
Damn it!

1007
01:20:00,713 --> 01:20:02,006
Damn it.

1008
01:20:07,220 --> 01:20:10,098
I knew it wouldn't take long,
but I couldn't get to it.

1009
01:20:10,181 --> 01:20:11,724
The tide was up.

1010
01:20:19,983 --> 01:20:21,109
Chuck!

1011
01:20:23,653 --> 01:20:24,821
Chuck!

1012
01:21:26,382 --> 01:21:27,633
Come on!

1013
01:22:03,002 --> 01:22:04,170
Chuck!

1014
01:22:04,754 --> 01:22:06,672
Where are you, Chuck?

1015
01:22:31,322 --> 01:22:32,532
Chuck!

1016
01:22:34,242 --> 01:22:35,409
Chuck!

1017
01:23:19,912 --> 01:23:21,289
Who are you?

1018
01:23:23,416 --> 01:23:26,252
I'm Teddy Daniels. I'm a cop.

1019
01:23:27,628 --> 01:23:29,338
You're the marshal.

1020
01:23:30,381 --> 01:23:31,799
That's right.

1021
01:23:34,135 --> 01:23:38,014
Would you mind taking your hand
from behind your back, please?

1022
01:23:38,097 --> 01:23:39,932
Why? Why?

1023
01:23:41,434 --> 01:23:44,437
I wanna make sure that
what you're holding won't hurt me.

1024
01:23:52,111 --> 01:23:53,821
I'm gonna keep this

1025
01:23:55,323 --> 01:23:56,824
if you don't mind.

1026
01:23:57,658 --> 01:23:59,076
Fine by me.

1027
01:24:08,127 --> 01:24:09,462
You're...

1028
01:24:10,880 --> 01:24:12,715
You're Rachel Solando.

1029
01:24:14,300 --> 01:24:15,718
The real one.

1030
01:24:19,722 --> 01:24:21,349
Did you kill your children?

1031
01:24:23,142 --> 01:24:24,977
I never had children.

1032
01:24:25,645 --> 01:24:27,438
I was never married.

1033
01:24:28,981 --> 01:24:32,526
And before I was a patient at Ashecliffe,
I worked here.

1034
01:24:33,152 --> 01:24:35,738
You... You were a nurse?

1035
01:24:38,074 --> 01:24:40,034
I was a doctor, Marshal.

1036
01:24:43,454 --> 01:24:45,164
You think I'm crazy.

1037
01:24:45,539 --> 01:24:48,876
- No. No, no, I never...
- And if I say I'm not crazy?

1038
01:24:50,086 --> 01:24:52,505
Well, that hardly helps, does it?

1039
01:24:53,339 --> 01:24:55,841
That's the Kafkaesque genius of it.

1040
01:24:59,136 --> 01:25:01,430
People tell the world you're crazy,

1041
01:25:01,514 --> 01:25:05,434
and all your protests to the contrary
just confirm what they're saying.

1042
01:25:06,018 --> 01:25:09,188
I'm not following you. I'm sorry.

1043
01:25:09,814 --> 01:25:11,774
Once you're declared insane,

1044
01:25:11,857 --> 01:25:15,361
then anything you do
is called part of that insanity.

1045
01:25:15,444 --> 01:25:21,033
Reasonable protests are denial.
Valid fears, paranoia.

1046
01:25:21,117 --> 01:25:25,204
Survival instincts
are defense mechanisms.

1047
01:25:25,496 --> 01:25:29,208
You're smarter than you look, Marshal.
That's probably not a good thing.

1048
01:25:30,084 --> 01:25:31,544
Tell me something.

1049
01:25:31,627 --> 01:25:32,753
Yeah.

1050
01:25:33,921 --> 01:25:35,715
What happened to you?

1051
01:25:36,549 --> 01:25:39,969
I started asking about these
large shipments of sodium amytal

1052
01:25:40,052 --> 01:25:41,804
and opium-based hallucinogens.

1053
01:25:41,887 --> 01:25:43,597
Psychotropic drugs.

1054
01:25:44,974 --> 01:25:47,351
I asked about the surgeries, too.

1055
01:25:49,395 --> 01:25:51,564
You ever heard of
a transorbital lobotomy?

1056
01:25:53,107 --> 01:25:55,818
They zap the patient with electroshock,

1057
01:25:55,901 --> 01:25:58,738
then go through the eye with an ice pick,

1058
01:26:00,906 --> 01:26:02,992
pull out some nerve fibers.

1059
01:26:05,411 --> 01:26:07,872
Makes the patients much more obedient.

1060
01:26:07,955 --> 01:26:09,290
Tractable.

1061
01:26:10,750 --> 01:26:12,251
It's barbaric,

1062
01:26:13,252 --> 01:26:14,754
unconscionable.

1063
01:26:15,755 --> 01:26:19,508
Do you know how pain
enters the body, Marshal? Do you?

1064
01:26:20,760 --> 01:26:22,219
Depends on where you're hurt?

1065
01:26:22,303 --> 01:26:27,475
No, it has nothing to do with the flesh.
The brain controls pain.

1066
01:26:28,100 --> 01:26:32,480
The brain controls fear, empathy, sleep,
hunger, anger. Everything.

1067
01:26:34,815 --> 01:26:36,609
What if you could control it?

1068
01:26:37,109 --> 01:26:38,569
You mean the brain?

1069
01:26:38,652 --> 01:26:45,451
Recreate a man so he doesn't feel
pain or love or sympathy.

1070
01:26:46,911 --> 01:26:48,371
A man who can't be interrogated,

1071
01:26:48,454 --> 01:26:51,165
because he has no memories
to confess.

1072
01:26:53,751 --> 01:26:57,421
You can never take away
all a man's memories. Never.

1073
01:26:57,505 --> 01:27:01,634
Marshal, the North Koreans
used American POWs

1074
01:27:01,717 --> 01:27:03,386
during their brainwashing experiments.

1075
01:27:03,469 --> 01:27:06,889
They turned soldiers into traitors.
That's what they're doing here.

1076
01:27:06,972 --> 01:27:09,058
They're creating ghosts
to go out in the world

1077
01:27:09,141 --> 01:27:12,395
and do things sane men...
Sane men never would.

1078
01:27:12,478 --> 01:27:15,815
To have that kind of ability,
that kind of knowledge,

1079
01:27:15,898 --> 01:27:18,150
- that would take years.
- Years. Years of research.

1080
01:27:18,651 --> 01:27:21,362
Hundreds of patients to experiment on.

1081
01:27:22,613 --> 01:27:25,032
Fifty years from now,
people will look back

1082
01:27:25,116 --> 01:27:28,494
and say, here, this place,
is where it all began.

1083
01:27:29,203 --> 01:27:33,999
The Nazis used the Jews, Soviets used
prisoners in their own Gulags,

1084
01:27:34,834 --> 01:27:38,295
and we tested patients
on Shutter Island.

1085
01:27:39,964 --> 01:27:41,632
No, they won't.

1086
01:27:42,591 --> 01:27:43,592
No.

1087
01:27:46,053 --> 01:27:48,180
You do understand

1088
01:27:50,724 --> 01:27:53,018
that they can't let you leave.

1089
01:27:53,310 --> 01:27:56,647
I am a federal marshal.
They can't stop me.

1090
01:27:58,023 --> 01:28:03,112
I was an esteemed psychiatrist
from a respected family.

1091
01:28:05,197 --> 01:28:06,824
Didn't matter.

1092
01:28:09,535 --> 01:28:11,120
Let me ask you.

1093
01:28:11,203 --> 01:28:13,581
Any past traumas in your life?

1094
01:28:14,957 --> 01:28:16,208
Yes.

1095
01:28:17,376 --> 01:28:19,462
But why would that matter?

1096
01:28:19,545 --> 01:28:21,839
Because they're gonna point
to some event in your past

1097
01:28:21,922 --> 01:28:24,425
and say it's the reason
you lost your sanity.

1098
01:28:24,508 --> 01:28:29,889
So that when they commit you here,
your friends and colleagues will say,

1099
01:28:29,972 --> 01:28:31,891
"Of course he cracked.

1100
01:28:32,892 --> 01:28:34,143
"Who wouldn't after what
he'd been through?"

1101
01:28:34,226 --> 01:28:36,729
They can say that about anyone,
anyone at all.

1102
01:28:36,812 --> 01:28:39,773
The point is
they're gonna say it about you.

1103
01:28:43,027 --> 01:28:44,653
How's your head?

1104
01:28:44,737 --> 01:28:46,822
My head?

1105
01:28:46,906 --> 01:28:50,326
Any funny dreams lately?
Trouble sleeping?

1106
01:28:52,536 --> 01:28:56,874
- Headaches?
- I am prone to migraines, yes.

1107
01:28:56,957 --> 01:28:58,250
Jesus.

1108
01:29:00,544 --> 01:29:04,048
You haven't taken any pills, have you?
I mean, even aspirin?

1109
01:29:04,131 --> 01:29:06,300
- The aspirin?
- Jesus.

1110
01:29:06,967 --> 01:29:10,679
And you ate the food in the cafeteria
and drank the coffee they gave you?

1111
01:29:10,763 --> 01:29:14,141
You tell me, at least, that you've
been smoking your own cigarettes.

1112
01:29:15,935 --> 01:29:17,144
No.

1113
01:29:18,103 --> 01:29:19,230
No.

1114
01:29:20,314 --> 01:29:21,690
No, I haven't.

1115
01:29:21,774 --> 01:29:24,527
It takes 36 to 48 hours
for neuroleptic narcotics

1116
01:29:24,610 --> 01:29:27,196
to reach workable levels
in the bloodstream.

1117
01:29:28,989 --> 01:29:30,824
Palsy comes first,

1118
01:29:31,742 --> 01:29:35,204
first the fingertips,
then eventually the whole hand.

1119
01:29:36,121 --> 01:29:40,292
Seen any walking nightmares
lately, Marshal?

1120
01:29:42,795 --> 01:29:45,756
Tell me what goes on in that lighthouse.

1121
01:29:46,632 --> 01:29:47,967
Tell me.

1122
01:29:49,134 --> 01:29:50,761
Brain surgery.

1123
01:29:51,428 --> 01:29:55,891
The let's-open-the-skull-and-see-
what-happens-if-we-pull-on-this kind.

1124
01:29:56,433 --> 01:29:59,311
The learned-it-from-the-Nazis kind.

1125
01:30:01,397 --> 01:30:03,857
That's where they create the ghosts.

1126
01:30:05,276 --> 01:30:09,154
Who knows about this?
On the island, I mean. Who?

1127
01:30:11,490 --> 01:30:12,741
Everyone.

1128
01:30:12,825 --> 01:30:16,537
Come on. The nurses? The orderlies?

1129
01:30:17,121 --> 01:30:20,416
- They couldn't possibly know...
- Everyone.

1130
01:30:39,351 --> 01:30:40,894
You can't stay here.

1131
01:30:41,520 --> 01:30:42,813
They think I'm dead, that I drowned.

1132
01:30:42,896 --> 01:30:45,899
I'm afraid if they come looking for you,
they might find me.

1133
01:30:45,983 --> 01:30:48,360
I'm sorry, but you have to go.

1134
01:30:54,992 --> 01:30:56,619
I'm gonna come back for you.

1135
01:30:56,702 --> 01:30:59,663
I won't be here. I move during the day.
New places every night.

1136
01:30:59,747 --> 01:31:02,082
But I could come get you,
get you off this island.

1137
01:31:02,166 --> 01:31:04,877
Haven't you heard a word I've said?

1138
01:31:04,960 --> 01:31:09,089
The only way off the island is the ferry,
and they control it.

1139
01:31:09,173 --> 01:31:11,216
You'll never leave here.

1140
01:31:20,559 --> 01:31:22,353
I had a friend.

1141
01:31:22,436 --> 01:31:25,981
I was with him yesterday,
but we got separated.

1142
01:31:26,065 --> 01:31:27,733
Have you seen him?

1143
01:31:28,901 --> 01:31:30,235
Marshal,

1144
01:31:31,779 --> 01:31:33,906
you have no friends.

1145
01:32:06,230 --> 01:32:07,773
There you are.

1146
01:32:10,609 --> 01:32:13,278
We were wondering
when you'd show up.

1147
01:32:14,905 --> 01:32:16,448
Have a seat.

1148
01:32:16,907 --> 01:32:18,200
Come on.

1149
01:32:28,877 --> 01:32:31,505
Taking a leisurely stroll, were we?

1150
01:32:32,589 --> 01:32:35,634
I was just looking around.

1151
01:32:38,595 --> 01:32:41,014
Did you enjoy God's latest gift?

1152
01:32:42,641 --> 01:32:43,976
- What?
- God's gift.

1153
01:32:46,145 --> 01:32:47,479
The violence.

1154
01:32:50,315 --> 01:32:54,695
When I came downstairs in my home
and I saw that tree in my living room,

1155
01:32:54,778 --> 01:32:58,615
it reached out for me like a divine hand.

1156
01:33:00,826 --> 01:33:02,661
God loves violence.

1157
01:33:05,330 --> 01:33:08,167
- I hadn't noticed.
- Sure you have.

1158
01:33:09,334 --> 01:33:14,465
Why else would there be so much of it?
It's in us. It's what we are.

1159
01:33:16,508 --> 01:33:18,844
We wage war, we burn sacrifices,

1160
01:33:18,927 --> 01:33:21,472
and pillage and plunder
and tear at the flesh of our brothers.

1161
01:33:21,555 --> 01:33:25,476
And why? Because God gave us
violence to wage in his honor.

1162
01:33:28,687 --> 01:33:31,106
I thought God gave us moral order.

1163
01:33:31,190 --> 01:33:34,193
There's no moral order
as pure as this storm.

1164
01:33:34,818 --> 01:33:37,112
There's no moral order at all.

1165
01:33:37,404 --> 01:33:40,949
There's just this,
can my violence conquer yours?

1166
01:33:46,538 --> 01:33:48,957
- I'm not violent.
- Yes, you are.

1167
01:33:50,083 --> 01:33:52,503
You're as violent as they come.

1168
01:33:53,212 --> 01:33:56,799
I know this
because I'm as violent as they come.

1169
01:33:56,882 --> 01:33:59,051
If the constraints of society were lifted,

1170
01:33:59,134 --> 01:34:01,804
and I was all that stood
between you and a meal,

1171
01:34:01,887 --> 01:34:05,682
you would crack my skull with a rock
and eat my meaty parts.

1172
01:34:07,226 --> 01:34:08,811
Wouldn't you?

1173
01:34:11,563 --> 01:34:14,024
Cawley thinks you're harmless,
that you can be controlled,

1174
01:34:14,107 --> 01:34:15,984
but I know different.

1175
01:34:16,610 --> 01:34:18,362
- You don't know me.
- Oh, but I do.

1176
01:34:18,445 --> 01:34:21,615
- No, you don't. You don't know me at all.
- Oh, I know you.

1177
01:34:21,698 --> 01:34:24,409
We've known each other for centuries.

1178
01:34:33,752 --> 01:34:36,672
If I was to sink my teeth
into your eye right now,

1179
01:34:36,755 --> 01:34:40,092
would you be able to stop me
before I blinded you?

1180
01:34:44,221 --> 01:34:45,848
Give it a try.

1181
01:34:47,391 --> 01:34:49,101
That's the spirit.

1182
01:35:23,844 --> 01:35:26,471
Don't worry, because we're going
to get you back to your room.

1183
01:35:28,098 --> 01:35:29,766
- Not really.
- Something I've seen.

1184
01:35:29,850 --> 01:35:31,101
Okay.

1185
01:35:36,315 --> 01:35:38,066
Where have you been?

1186
01:35:38,150 --> 01:35:40,903
Oh, just wandering.
Just looking at your island.

1187
01:35:40,986 --> 01:35:44,656
Oh, I forgot you're leaving
now that Rachel's been found.

1188
01:35:45,490 --> 01:35:46,909
- Stop looking at him.
- For sure. Yeah.

1189
01:35:46,992 --> 01:35:50,245
Stop looking at him. Stop looking at him.

1190
01:35:50,329 --> 01:35:52,331
- Big meeting?
- Oh, yes.

1191
01:35:52,414 --> 01:35:54,082
- It's okay. I'm...
- I don't like that.

1192
01:35:54,166 --> 01:35:56,168
Apparently there was
an unidentified man

1193
01:35:56,251 --> 01:35:57,544
in Ward C yesterday.

1194
01:35:57,628 --> 01:36:01,006
He subdued a highly dangerous patient
quite handily.

1195
01:36:01,590 --> 01:36:02,591
Is that so?

1196
01:36:02,674 --> 01:36:05,135
It seems he had a long conversation
with a paranoid schizophrenic,

1197
01:36:05,218 --> 01:36:06,428
George Noyce.

1198
01:36:06,511 --> 01:36:09,306
Well, I don't remember
what I'm supposed to remember.

1199
01:36:09,389 --> 01:36:11,099
We're gated down. We're fine.

1200
01:36:11,183 --> 01:36:15,228
This Noyce, you said
his name was, he's delusional?

1201
01:36:15,312 --> 01:36:18,023
Extremely. He can be quite upsetting.

1202
01:36:18,106 --> 01:36:19,816
As a matter of fact, two weeks ago,

1203
01:36:19,900 --> 01:36:24,363
a patient got so wound up by one
of Noyce's stories that he beat him up.

1204
01:36:25,614 --> 01:36:27,032
Cigarette?

1205
01:36:28,825 --> 01:36:30,619
No, thanks. I quit.

1206
01:36:31,703 --> 01:36:35,749
- So you're taking the ferry?
- Yes, absolutely.

1207
01:36:35,832 --> 01:36:39,294
I think we've gotten
all we came here for, so...

1208
01:36:39,378 --> 01:36:40,712
"We," Marshal?

1209
01:36:42,714 --> 01:36:46,301
Speaking of which,
have you seen him, Doctor?

1210
01:36:46,385 --> 01:36:47,552
Who?

1211
01:36:48,387 --> 01:36:50,097
My partner, Chuck.

1212
01:36:52,432 --> 01:36:55,268
You don't have a partner, Marshal.
You came here alone.

1213
01:36:57,729 --> 01:36:59,898
You know, I've built
something valuable here,

1214
01:36:59,982 --> 01:37:03,151
and valuable things have a way of
being misunderstood in their own time.

1215
01:37:03,235 --> 01:37:05,320
Everyone wants a quick fix.
They always have.

1216
01:37:05,404 --> 01:37:08,991
I'm trying to do something that people,
yourself included, don't understand.

1217
01:37:09,074 --> 01:37:12,035
And I'm not going to give up
without a fight.

1218
01:37:13,870 --> 01:37:15,497
I can see that.

1219
01:37:19,584 --> 01:37:22,212
So, tell me again about your partner.

1220
01:37:23,922 --> 01:37:25,549
What partner?

1221
01:37:28,301 --> 01:37:29,386
It's fine.

1222
01:38:17,726 --> 01:38:21,521
She made a mess. I cleaned it up.
She made a mess again.

1223
01:38:30,822 --> 01:38:32,199
Marshal,

1224
01:38:33,575 --> 01:38:35,202
going somewhere?

1225
01:38:35,494 --> 01:38:38,663
I'm just heading out to the ferry, so...

1226
01:38:39,164 --> 01:38:42,709
Oh, well, I'm afraid it's the other way.

1227
01:38:45,670 --> 01:38:50,342
If you'll wait a moment, I'll find you
someone who can take you to the dock.

1228
01:38:55,013 --> 01:38:58,850
- What's this, Doctor? What's this?
- It's just a sedative.

1229
01:38:58,934 --> 01:39:02,104
- A precaution.
- A precaution.

1230
01:39:05,023 --> 01:39:09,111
What are you going to do?
Kill me? Marshal.

1231
01:39:09,486 --> 01:39:11,029
You think you deserve it?

1232
01:39:11,113 --> 01:39:13,907
For what? Provoking you?

1233
01:39:14,699 --> 01:39:17,536
Well, forgive me.
What doesn't provoke you?

1234
01:39:18,078 --> 01:39:21,206
- Remarks? Words?
- Nazis?

1235
01:39:21,665 --> 01:39:25,710
Well, that, too.
And, of course, memories, dreams.

1236
01:39:26,795 --> 01:39:31,049
Did you know that the word "trauma"
comes from the Greek for "wound"?

1237
01:39:31,716 --> 01:39:34,469
And what is the German word
for "dream"?

1238
01:39:38,098 --> 01:39:41,059
Wounds can create monsters,
and you...

1239
01:39:41,726 --> 01:39:44,104
You are wounded, Marshal.

1240
01:39:45,147 --> 01:39:48,316
And wouldn't you agree,
when you see a monster,

1241
01:39:49,025 --> 01:39:50,777
you must stop it?

1242
01:39:51,361 --> 01:39:52,571
Yeah.

1243
01:39:53,738 --> 01:39:55,574
- I agree.
- Yes.

1244
01:39:56,408 --> 01:39:57,492
Yeah.

1245
01:40:14,718 --> 01:40:16,970
I told him that we'd take
about an hour to do it.

1246
01:40:17,053 --> 01:40:20,140
Yeah. Did they say
we're going to do the first floor?

1247
01:40:20,223 --> 01:40:21,474
How long you been on the clock?

1248
01:40:21,558 --> 01:40:25,270
- I've been on for 18 hours straight.
- Nice paycheck.

1249
01:40:42,412 --> 01:40:44,497
What are you doing, baby?

1250
01:40:49,294 --> 01:40:51,796
- You gotta get to the ferry.
- No.

1251
01:40:52,547 --> 01:40:53,840
No, no.

1252
01:40:55,050 --> 01:40:56,218
Yeah.

1253
01:40:57,344 --> 01:41:02,224
If the world thinks that Chuck is dead,
then he's perfect for their experiments.

1254
01:41:03,308 --> 01:41:05,560
There's only one place they'd take him.

1255
01:41:08,188 --> 01:41:09,814
You go there and you'll die.

1256
01:41:09,898 --> 01:41:11,566
He's my partner. If they are hurting him,

1257
01:41:11,650 --> 01:41:14,819
if they're holding him against his will,
I've gotta bring him out.

1258
01:41:14,903 --> 01:41:16,947
I can't lose anyone else.

1259
01:41:17,030 --> 01:41:18,281
Don't go, Teddy, please.

1260
01:41:18,365 --> 01:41:21,785
- Please, don't do this. Don't go.
- I'm sorry, honey.

1261
01:41:25,372 --> 01:41:27,165
I'm sorry, honey.

1262
01:41:28,250 --> 01:41:31,294
I love this thing
because you gave it to me,

1263
01:41:33,672 --> 01:41:35,507
but the truth is

1264
01:41:37,175 --> 01:41:39,344
it is one fucking ugly tie.

1265
01:42:19,551 --> 01:42:20,719
No.

1266
01:43:42,634 --> 01:43:44,010
Don't move. Stay where you are.

1267
01:43:46,012 --> 01:43:47,430
Are you gonna kill me?

1268
01:43:49,099 --> 01:43:51,643
No, I'm not gonna kill you.

1269
01:45:44,255 --> 01:45:46,132
Why are you all wet, baby?

1270
01:45:48,343 --> 01:45:51,596
- What did you say?
- You know exactly what I said.

1271
01:46:04,692 --> 01:46:06,945
The rifle's empty, by the way.

1272
01:46:13,451 --> 01:46:14,953
Have a seat.

1273
01:46:21,459 --> 01:46:23,878
For God's sake, dry off.
You'll catch cold.

1274
01:46:25,505 --> 01:46:26,631
All right.

1275
01:46:30,176 --> 01:46:32,095
How badly did you hurt the guard?

1276
01:46:33,805 --> 01:46:36,808
I don't know what you're talking about.

1277
01:46:39,978 --> 01:46:41,896
Yes, he's here.

1278
01:46:41,980 --> 01:46:45,984
Have Dr. Sheehan take a look at
your man before you send him up.

1279
01:46:46,067 --> 01:46:50,780
So Dr. Sheehan came in
on the ferry this morning, huh?

1280
01:46:51,739 --> 01:46:53,241
Not exactly.

1281
01:46:54,284 --> 01:46:57,328
You blew up my car.
I really loved that car.

1282
01:46:58,246 --> 01:47:00,331
Sorry to hear about that.

1283
01:47:03,626 --> 01:47:06,004
Tremors are getting pretty bad.

1284
01:47:06,629 --> 01:47:09,048
How are the hallucinations?

1285
01:47:09,132 --> 01:47:11,426
Get out of here, Teddy.

1286
01:47:11,509 --> 01:47:13,303
This place is gonna be the end of you.

1287
01:47:17,056 --> 01:47:18,182
Not bad.

1288
01:47:18,266 --> 01:47:20,852
- They'll get worse.
- I know.

1289
01:47:21,728 --> 01:47:26,024
Dr. Solando,
she told me about the neuroleptics.

1290
01:47:26,566 --> 01:47:29,027
Did she, now? And when was this?

1291
01:47:29,110 --> 01:47:33,906
I found her, Doctor,
in a cave out by the cliffs.

1292
01:47:33,990 --> 01:47:35,366
But you'll never get to her.

1293
01:47:35,450 --> 01:47:38,870
I don't doubt it,
considering she's not real.

1294
01:47:41,080 --> 01:47:44,208
Your delusions are more severe
than I thought.

1295
01:47:45,418 --> 01:47:47,587
You're not on neuroleptics.

1296
01:47:48,046 --> 01:47:49,922
You're not on anything,
as a matter of fact.

1297
01:47:50,006 --> 01:47:52,634
Then what the fuck is this?
What the fuck is this?

1298
01:47:52,717 --> 01:47:53,718
Withdrawal.

1299
01:47:54,719 --> 01:47:56,679
Withdrawal? From what?

1300
01:47:56,763 --> 01:47:59,098
I haven't had a goddamn drink
since I've been on this island.

1301
01:47:59,182 --> 01:48:00,808
Chlorpromazine.

1302
01:48:01,643 --> 01:48:05,313
I'm not a fan of pharmacology,
but I have to say, in your case...

1303
01:48:05,396 --> 01:48:08,650
- Chloraproma-what?
- Chlorpromazine.

1304
01:48:08,733 --> 01:48:12,737
The same thing we've been giving you
for the past 24 months.

1305
01:48:14,030 --> 01:48:16,157
So for the past two years, you...

1306
01:48:16,240 --> 01:48:19,535
You've had somebody slipping me drugs
in Boston. Is that it?

1307
01:48:19,619 --> 01:48:21,079
Not Boston.

1308
01:48:21,579 --> 01:48:22,747
Here.

1309
01:48:23,539 --> 01:48:27,502
You've been here for two years.
A patient of this institution.

1310
01:48:31,255 --> 01:48:35,009
After everything I've seen here, Doctor,

1311
01:48:35,093 --> 01:48:38,513
you really think you're gonna
convince me I'm crazy?

1312
01:48:38,596 --> 01:48:40,556
Do you know the kind of people
that I deal with every day?

1313
01:48:40,640 --> 01:48:42,517
I'm a U.S. Marshal, for God's sakes.

1314
01:48:42,600 --> 01:48:44,477
You were a U.S. Marshal.

1315
01:48:44,560 --> 01:48:48,356
Here's a copy of the intake form
you broke into Ward C for.

1316
01:48:48,439 --> 01:48:49,816
Proof of the 67th patient.

1317
01:48:49,899 --> 01:48:51,067
If you'd gotten it to the mainland,

1318
01:48:51,150 --> 01:48:52,944
you could have
blown the lid off this place.

1319
01:48:53,027 --> 01:48:54,153
Wait. Where did... Where did you...

1320
01:48:54,237 --> 01:48:56,030
Yet somehow,
you couldn't find time to look at it.

1321
01:48:56,114 --> 01:48:57,824
Well, read it now.

1322
01:48:58,282 --> 01:48:59,659
Go ahead.

1323
01:49:03,454 --> 01:49:07,291
"Patient is highly intelligent, highly
delusional decorated Army veteran.

1324
01:49:07,375 --> 01:49:11,129
"Present for the liberation of Dachau.

1325
01:49:11,212 --> 01:49:13,840
"Former U.S. Marshal.
Known proclivity for violence.

1326
01:49:13,923 --> 01:49:17,176
"Shows no remorse for his crime
because he denies the crime ever...

1327
01:49:17,260 --> 01:49:18,302
"Ever took place.

1328
01:49:18,386 --> 01:49:20,263
"Highly developed
and fantastical narratives,

1329
01:49:20,346 --> 01:49:22,724
"which preclude facing
the truth of his actions."

1330
01:49:22,807 --> 01:49:23,891
I've had enough of this bullshit!

1331
01:49:23,975 --> 01:49:27,854
Where's my partner? Where's Chuck?
Where is he?

1332
01:49:27,937 --> 01:49:29,647
Let's try this another way.

1333
01:49:29,731 --> 01:49:32,275
Your wife's maiden name was Chanal,
am I correct?

1334
01:49:32,358 --> 01:49:33,776
Don't you even talk about her.
Don't you...

1335
01:49:33,860 --> 01:49:35,737
I'm afraid I have to.

1336
01:49:37,822 --> 01:49:42,034
Notice anything these four names
have in common? It's your rule of four.

1337
01:49:42,118 --> 01:49:43,244
Andrew, what do you see?

1338
01:49:43,327 --> 01:49:46,330
If you've done anything to my partner,
Doctor, that is a violation of...

1339
01:49:46,414 --> 01:49:48,833
Focus, Andrew! What do you see?

1340
01:49:49,834 --> 01:49:52,336
The names have the same letters.

1341
01:49:53,212 --> 01:49:56,632
Edward Daniels has exactly
the same 13 letters as Andrew Laeddis.

1342
01:49:56,716 --> 01:49:58,926
The same as Rachel Solando
and Dolores Chanal.

1343
01:49:59,010 --> 01:50:01,095
The names are anagrams
for each other.

1344
01:50:01,179 --> 01:50:03,765
Your tactics,
they're not gonna work on me.

1345
01:50:03,848 --> 01:50:06,642
You came here for the truth. Here it is.

1346
01:50:06,726 --> 01:50:08,728
Your name is Andrew Laeddis.

1347
01:50:08,811 --> 01:50:12,356
The 67th patient at Ashecliffe
is you, Andrew.

1348
01:50:14,192 --> 01:50:15,151
Bullshit.

1349
01:50:15,234 --> 01:50:17,445
You were committed here by court order
24 months ago.

1350
01:50:17,528 --> 01:50:20,865
Your crime is terrible,
one you can't forgive yourself for,

1351
01:50:20,948 --> 01:50:23,326
so you invented another self.

1352
01:50:25,495 --> 01:50:26,913
All right.

1353
01:50:27,413 --> 01:50:30,082
Let's get down to the facts, all right?

1354
01:50:30,166 --> 01:50:33,044
You've created a story
in which you're not a murderer.

1355
01:50:33,127 --> 01:50:35,171
You're a hero, still a U.S. Marshal,

1356
01:50:35,254 --> 01:50:37,173
only here at Ashecliffe
because of a case,

1357
01:50:37,256 --> 01:50:40,593
and you've uncovered a conspiracy
so that anything we tell you

1358
01:50:40,676 --> 01:50:44,514
about who you are, what you've done,
you can dismiss as lies, Andrew.

1359
01:50:44,597 --> 01:50:45,890
My name is Edward Daniels.

1360
01:50:45,973 --> 01:50:50,228
I've been hearing this fantasy for
two years now. I know every detail.

1361
01:50:50,311 --> 01:50:52,271
Patient 67, the storm,

1362
01:50:52,355 --> 01:50:55,566
Rachel Solando, your missing partner,
the dreams you have every night.

1363
01:50:55,650 --> 01:50:58,069
You were at Dachau,
but you may not have killed any guards.

1364
01:51:02,114 --> 01:51:05,785
I wish I could let you just live
in your fantasy world.

1365
01:51:05,868 --> 01:51:07,328
I really do.

1366
01:51:08,204 --> 01:51:10,414
But you're violent, trained, dangerous.

1367
01:51:10,498 --> 01:51:12,792
You're the most dangerous patient
we have.

1368
01:51:12,875 --> 01:51:15,169
You've injured orderlies, guards,
other patients.

1369
01:51:15,253 --> 01:51:17,171
Two weeks ago,
you attacked George Noyce.

1370
01:51:17,255 --> 01:51:19,507
No, no. I am fucking on to you, Doctor.

1371
01:51:19,590 --> 01:51:21,467
- You had Noyce beaten.
- Of course I didn't!

1372
01:51:21,551 --> 01:51:23,636
Give me one reason
why I would even touch him!

1373
01:51:23,719 --> 01:51:26,097
Because he called you Laeddis,

1374
01:51:26,180 --> 01:51:29,225
and you'd do anything not to be him.

1375
01:51:29,308 --> 01:51:32,895
I have a transcript of the conversation
you had with Noyce yesterday.

1376
01:51:32,979 --> 01:51:37,024
"This is about you, and, Laeddis,
that's all it's ever been about."

1377
01:51:38,943 --> 01:51:41,445
No, no. He's saying
this is about me and Laeddis.

1378
01:51:41,529 --> 01:51:43,406
When you asked him
what happened to his face,

1379
01:51:43,489 --> 01:51:46,868
he said, now here I'm quoting again,
"You did this."

1380
01:51:46,951 --> 01:51:49,078
No, no, he meant that it was my fault.

1381
01:51:49,161 --> 01:51:51,163
You almost killed him.

1382
01:51:52,832 --> 01:51:55,626
The warden and the Board of Overseers
are determined something be done.

1383
01:51:55,710 --> 01:51:57,420
It's been decided

1384
01:51:57,503 --> 01:52:02,133
that unless we can bring you
back to sanity now, right now,

1385
01:52:02,216 --> 01:52:05,636
permanent measures will be taken to
ensure you can't hurt anyone ever again.

1386
01:52:09,140 --> 01:52:12,476
They'll lobotomize you, Andrew.
Do you understand?

1387
01:52:16,731 --> 01:52:18,649
Yeah, I understand.

1388
01:52:19,483 --> 01:52:21,694
I understand just fine.

1389
01:52:22,320 --> 01:52:26,407
If I don't play along
with your little game here,

1390
01:52:26,490 --> 01:52:29,619
Dr. Naehring's gonna turn me
into one of his ghosts.

1391
01:52:30,077 --> 01:52:31,454
But what about my partner?

1392
01:52:31,537 --> 01:52:36,000
You gonna tell the U.S. Marshal's office
that he's a defense mechanism?

1393
01:52:37,877 --> 01:52:39,337
Hello, boss.

1394
01:52:56,187 --> 01:52:58,981
What the fuck is going on here?

1395
01:53:01,859 --> 01:53:05,488
You working for him?

1396
01:53:06,322 --> 01:53:07,823
I'm sorry. There wasn't any other way.

1397
01:53:07,907 --> 01:53:10,826
Someone had to stick with you,
keep you safe.

1398
01:53:13,704 --> 01:53:15,831
You been watching me, huh?

1399
01:53:16,791 --> 01:53:18,876
Watching me every minute.

1400
01:53:19,794 --> 01:53:22,797
Who are you? Who are you? Tell me.

1401
01:53:23,589 --> 01:53:25,591
Don't you recognize me, Andrew?

1402
01:53:27,009 --> 01:53:30,721
I've been your primary psychiatrist
for the last two years.

1403
01:53:31,305 --> 01:53:33,182
I'm Lester Sheehan.

1404
01:53:39,647 --> 01:53:42,316
- I told you... I told you about my wife, I...
- I know.

1405
01:53:42,400 --> 01:53:45,653
I climbed down a cliff to get you.
I trusted you.

1406
01:53:45,736 --> 01:53:49,365
I risked everything to come
in here after you. Everything!

1407
01:53:49,448 --> 01:53:50,491
I know, boss.

1408
01:53:50,574 --> 01:53:53,369
We're running out of time here, Andrew.

1409
01:53:53,744 --> 01:53:55,329
I swore before the Board of Overseers

1410
01:53:55,413 --> 01:53:59,333
that I could construct the most radical,
cutting-edge role-play

1411
01:53:59,417 --> 01:54:01,669
ever attempted in psychiatry,
and it would bring you back.

1412
01:54:01,752 --> 01:54:04,797
I thought that if we let you play this out

1413
01:54:04,880 --> 01:54:08,509
we could get you to see
how untrue, how impossible it is.

1414
01:54:09,593 --> 01:54:12,054
You've had the run of the place
for two days.

1415
01:54:12,138 --> 01:54:15,433
Tell me, where are
the Nazi experiments?

1416
01:54:15,516 --> 01:54:17,309
The satanic ORs?

1417
01:54:30,948 --> 01:54:32,825
Andrew, listen to me.

1418
01:54:35,202 --> 01:54:37,455
If we fail with you,

1419
01:54:37,538 --> 01:54:41,459
then everything that we've tried to do
here will be discredited. Everything.

1420
01:54:43,586 --> 01:54:46,756
We're on the front lines
of a war here, old boy.

1421
01:54:47,506 --> 01:54:50,384
And right now, it all comes down to you.

1422
01:54:57,308 --> 01:55:00,019
- Don't move! Don't move!
- Andrew! Andrew! No. No.

1423
01:55:00,102 --> 01:55:03,314
My name is Edward Daniels!

1424
01:55:03,397 --> 01:55:05,441
This one's loaded.
I can tell by the weight.

1425
01:55:05,524 --> 01:55:08,110
I see. And that's your firearm, Marshal?
You're sure?

1426
01:55:08,194 --> 01:55:09,403
My initials are on the side.

1427
01:55:09,487 --> 01:55:11,781
There's a dent in the barrel
from when Philip Stacks shot at me.

1428
01:55:11,864 --> 01:55:13,991
You're not gonna fuck with my mind
on this one, Doctor!

1429
01:55:14,075 --> 01:55:15,117
Then blast away.

1430
01:55:15,201 --> 01:55:18,537
Because that's the only way
you're ever getting off this island.

1431
01:55:24,627 --> 01:55:26,504
Andrew, please don't.

1432
01:55:37,389 --> 01:55:38,682
My gun.

1433
01:55:45,272 --> 01:55:47,858
What did you do to my goddamn gun?

1434
01:55:48,275 --> 01:55:49,443
It's a toy, Andrew.

1435
01:55:52,947 --> 01:55:55,032
We're telling you the truth.

1436
01:55:55,533 --> 01:55:58,786
Dolores was insane,
manic-depressive, suicidal.

1437
01:55:59,453 --> 01:56:02,540
You drank, stayed away,
ignored what everyone told you.

1438
01:56:02,623 --> 01:56:03,749
You moved to that lake house

1439
01:56:03,833 --> 01:56:06,961
after she purposely set
your city apartment on fire.

1440
01:56:07,044 --> 01:56:08,337
- You were...
- You're lying.

1441
01:56:08,420 --> 01:56:11,882
- Andrew! Andrew, stop. No.
- You drugged the cigarettes!

1442
01:56:11,966 --> 01:56:13,801
- All you've done is lie!
- Andrew. Andrew.

1443
01:56:13,884 --> 01:56:17,096
Your children. Andrew, your children.

1444
01:56:17,179 --> 01:56:19,849
Simon. Henry.

1445
01:56:20,224 --> 01:56:21,517
I never had any children.

1446
01:56:21,600 --> 01:56:25,646
Your wife drowned them
at the cabin by the lake.

1447
01:56:25,729 --> 01:56:28,941
And here, the little girl,
the one you dream of

1448
01:56:29,650 --> 01:56:31,318
every night.

1449
01:56:31,402 --> 01:56:32,570
I never had a little girl.

1450
01:56:32,653 --> 01:56:36,240
The one who tells you over and over
that you should have saved her,

1451
01:56:36,323 --> 01:56:38,242
saved them all.

1452
01:56:38,325 --> 01:56:40,786
Your daughter, her name was Rachel.

1453
01:56:40,870 --> 01:56:43,747
Are you going to deny
that she ever lived?

1454
01:56:44,498 --> 01:56:46,250
Andrew, are you?

1455
01:57:09,231 --> 01:57:11,317
I'm so sorry, baby.

1456
01:57:15,696 --> 01:57:18,073
I told you not to come in here.

1457
01:57:18,532 --> 01:57:22,494
I told you this would be the end of you.

1458
01:57:42,848 --> 01:57:44,183
I'm back!

1459
01:57:44,808 --> 01:57:47,561
We got him just outside of Oklahoma.

1460
01:57:47,645 --> 01:57:50,189
Must've stopped 10 places
in between here and Tulsa.

1461
01:57:50,272 --> 01:57:52,358
I could sleep for a week.

1462
01:57:56,320 --> 01:57:57,655
Dolores?

1463
01:58:04,536 --> 01:58:05,871
Dolores?

1464
01:58:10,668 --> 01:58:12,962
<i>And he said, "Take up your bed
and walk." But God?</i>

1465
01:58:13,045 --> 01:58:14,088
Dolores?

1466
01:58:14,171 --> 01:58:18,259
<i>Then he said, "Take up your bed
and walk." Forgive sins, but God?</i>

1467
01:58:28,519 --> 01:58:29,895
Dolores?

1468
01:58:55,212 --> 01:58:56,463
Baby,

1469
01:58:58,507 --> 01:59:00,384
why are you all wet?

1470
01:59:02,720 --> 01:59:04,263
I missed you.

1471
01:59:11,645 --> 01:59:13,314
I wanna go home.

1472
01:59:16,442 --> 01:59:17,943
You are home.

1473
01:59:23,115 --> 01:59:24,950
Where are the kids?

1474
01:59:28,996 --> 01:59:30,748
They're in school.

1475
01:59:34,918 --> 01:59:36,920
It's Saturday, honey.

1476
01:59:38,088 --> 01:59:40,299
School's not in on Saturday.

1477
01:59:42,926 --> 01:59:44,553
My school is.

1478
01:59:57,900 --> 01:59:59,443
Oh, my God.

1479
02:00:01,737 --> 02:00:03,197
Oh, my God!

1480
02:00:16,335 --> 02:00:19,046
Oh, my God. Oh, my God.

1481
02:00:23,217 --> 02:00:24,802
Oh, my God, no.

1482
02:00:29,264 --> 02:00:30,974
Come on, come on.

1483
02:00:44,196 --> 02:00:47,324
No. No. Please, God.

1484
02:00:49,326 --> 02:00:53,122
Please, God, no! No!

1485
02:00:56,333 --> 02:00:57,459
No.

1486
02:01:02,965 --> 02:01:04,091
No.

1487
02:01:06,593 --> 02:01:07,845
No.

1488
02:01:52,222 --> 02:01:53,432
Baby.

1489
02:02:12,242 --> 02:02:14,745
Let's put them at the table, Andrew.

1490
02:02:15,579 --> 02:02:18,790
We'll dry them off.
We'll change their clothes.

1491
02:02:20,959 --> 02:02:23,086
They'll be our living dolls.

1492
02:02:27,424 --> 02:02:30,177
Tomorrow we can take them on a picnic.

1493
02:02:35,182 --> 02:02:39,686
If you ever loved me, Dolores,
please stop talking.

1494
02:02:46,276 --> 02:02:47,778
I love you.

1495
02:02:56,495 --> 02:02:58,080
Set me free.

1496
02:03:02,751 --> 02:03:04,169
Oh, baby.

1497
02:03:07,631 --> 02:03:09,550
We'll give them baths.

1498
02:03:12,803 --> 02:03:16,014
- I love you, baby.
- I love you, too.

1499
02:03:16,098 --> 02:03:17,891
- I love you so much.
- I love you so much.

1500
02:03:17,975 --> 02:03:19,726
I love you. I...

1501
02:03:43,584 --> 02:03:45,335
Oh, baby.

1502
02:03:51,300 --> 02:03:52,634
Andrew.

1503
02:03:54,678 --> 02:03:56,680
Andrew, can you hear me?

1504
02:03:56,972 --> 02:03:58,307
Rachel.

1505
02:03:59,182 --> 02:04:00,851
Rachel, Rachel.

1506
02:04:03,103 --> 02:04:04,396
Rachel?

1507
02:04:06,898 --> 02:04:08,358
Rachel who?

1508
02:04:11,236 --> 02:04:13,322
Rachel. Rachel Laeddis.

1509
02:04:14,489 --> 02:04:16,241
My daughter.

1510
02:04:19,828 --> 02:04:21,580
Why are you here?

1511
02:04:24,791 --> 02:04:26,335
Because I killed my wife.

1512
02:04:26,418 --> 02:04:28,545
And why did you do that?

1513
02:04:32,049 --> 02:04:35,218
Because she murdered our children,

1514
02:04:38,138 --> 02:04:39,556
and she told me to let her go.

1515
02:04:43,727 --> 02:04:46,897
- Who's Teddy Daniels?
- He doesn't exist.

1516
02:04:49,232 --> 02:04:51,693
Neither does Rachel Solando.
I made them up.

1517
02:04:51,777 --> 02:04:53,028
Why?

1518
02:04:54,363 --> 02:04:56,531
We need to hear you say it.

1519
02:05:02,329 --> 02:05:05,540
After she tried to kill herself
the first time,

1520
02:05:07,584 --> 02:05:09,544
Dolores told me she...

1521
02:05:10,504 --> 02:05:14,758
She had an insect living
inside her brain.

1522
02:05:16,760 --> 02:05:21,473
She could feel it
clicking across her skull,

1523
02:05:21,556 --> 02:05:25,769
just pulling the wires just for fun.

1524
02:05:29,439 --> 02:05:31,233
She told me that.

1525
02:05:32,693 --> 02:05:35,529
She told me that, but I didn't listen.

1526
02:05:39,241 --> 02:05:41,535
I loved her so much, you know.

1527
02:05:42,953 --> 02:05:45,122
Why did you make them up?

1528
02:05:47,207 --> 02:05:51,128
Because I can't take knowing
that Dolores killed our children.

1529
02:05:54,965 --> 02:05:56,299
And I...

1530
02:05:58,802 --> 02:06:03,306
I killed them 'cause I didn't get her help,
you know.

1531
02:06:07,519 --> 02:06:09,146
I killed them.

1532
02:06:13,942 --> 02:06:15,068
Here's my fear, Andrew.

1533
02:06:15,152 --> 02:06:18,363
We broke through once before,
nine months ago,

1534
02:06:18,447 --> 02:06:19,448
and then you regressed.

1535
02:06:21,992 --> 02:06:25,328
- I don't remember that.
- I know.

1536
02:06:26,830 --> 02:06:28,623
You reset, Andrew.

1537
02:06:29,082 --> 02:06:33,170
Like a tape playing over and over
on an endless loop.

1538
02:06:34,421 --> 02:06:35,881
I hope that what we've done here
will be enough

1539
02:06:35,964 --> 02:06:39,092
to stop it from ever happening again,

1540
02:06:39,176 --> 02:06:42,679
but I need to know
you've accepted reality.

1541
02:06:49,186 --> 02:06:51,938
You came after me, huh, Doctor?

1542
02:06:53,815 --> 02:06:57,694
You tried to help me
when no one else would.

1543
02:07:09,498 --> 02:07:12,375
My name's Andrew Laeddis,

1544
02:07:19,382 --> 02:07:22,844
and I murdered my wife
in the spring of '52.

1545
02:07:47,577 --> 02:07:51,039
- How we doing this morning?
- Good.

1546
02:07:51,122 --> 02:07:54,042
- And you?
- Can't complain.

1547
02:08:03,718 --> 02:08:07,681
- So what's our next move?
- You tell me.

1548
02:08:13,270 --> 02:08:17,566
We gotta get off this rock, Chuck.
Get back to the mainland.

1549
02:08:17,649 --> 02:08:20,610
Whatever the hell's going on here,
it's bad.

1550
02:08:42,549 --> 02:08:45,760
Don't worry, partner,
they're not gonna catch us.

1551
02:08:51,308 --> 02:08:54,144
That's right. We're too smart for them.

1552
02:08:55,270 --> 02:08:57,397
Yeah, we are, aren't we?

1553
02:09:13,038 --> 02:09:15,790
You know,
this place makes me wonder...

1554
02:09:16,333 --> 02:09:18,418
Yeah, what's that, boss?

1555
02:09:19,377 --> 02:09:21,338
Which would be worse,

1556
02:09:22,172 --> 02:09:26,301
to live as a monster
or to die as a good man?

1557
02:09:36,144 --> 02:09:37,437
Teddy?

